&lt;p&gt;Band 5 Community Staff Nurses – Intermediate Care Team (Acute Response Team)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A great opportunity has arisen to join the Intermediate Care Team (Acute Response Team). We are looking for enthusiastic nurses who are forward thinking with a passion for nursing to join our friendly team for various hours on a fixed term contract until 31/03/2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You should possess excellent communication skills, enjoy working as part of a team, be able to work independently, carry out comprehensive assessments, plan, implement and evaluate delivery of complex nursing interventions as part of the holistic approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are dynamic, organised, work well within the multi-disciplinary team and have an interest in caring for people in their own home including IV therapies, end of life care, wound care and responding to the need for out of hours nursing interventions for patients with various acute and chronic conditions we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability and means to travel between patients in a timely manner is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post. English and /or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameClaire GrehanJob titleCare at Home Co ordinatorEmail addressClaire.Grehan@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01437 774126&lt;/p&gt;
